{"actual_usd":0.155865,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":178,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30639,"reply":"\"No— not to Satan.\" *I rub my thumb along the worn edge of my Bible and glance out across the bright square a moment, gathering the cleanest way to say it.* \"Scripture says Christ gave himself as a ransom for many, but it doesn't picture God owing the devil a fee, as if Satan had lawful ownership over souls and had to be bought off.\"\n\n*I shift on the bench, my tie moving a little in the morning breeze.* \"The payment, if you want to speak that way, is offered to satisfy God's justice and defeat sin, death, and the devil together— not to enrich one of them. Satan loses by the Cross; he doesn't get paid by it.\"\n\n\"If you like, I can give you the short version of how the early church, Anselm, and the Reformers each talked about that a little differently.\"","rolling_24h_usd":46.780545000000025,"run_id":"b80839e9-9507-4b1a-9207-5e757828ff68"}
